values: My doctor gave me Xanax. Which will help me immensely in social situations, especially tomorrow at a party I'm going to. But he seems to think that the Xanax will be enough to help me get through my plane trip to FL at the end of the month. HA. Again, I say HA. I dont know what to do. I am so incredibly scared and I seriously think I need something much much stronger. I'm thinking of hypnosis.

My leg has been numb for a few weeks now. Maybe I should correct that....you know how, when you sit on your foot and it falls asleep and you touch it and it feels all weird, like, you KNOW you're touching it but it doesnt feel like it? My leg has been like that. When I shave my leg, it's weird, like I KNOW I'm shaving it, but it feels asleep. Its only 1 leg. From below knee to above ankle. Weird, huh? I can feel my hypchodiacism setting in....maybe it's a sign of cancer, or worse! Ahhh.....damn WebMD doesnt have ANY help! I could be dying,...

Joe thinks I'll be boring at OCTA this year because I usually say I'm going to really party then I fall asleep early. :) But this year, hopefully I'll get to hang out with my bf and my bf always brings out my wild and crazy side. :) :) :)

I. Am. Depressed. And I just realized it. The stress of not knowing why we can't create life is getting to me. I hold my neice and I think "Why can't I have one?". I dont even know how to put it into words. Not really. The way I say it is just not correct. I cry everytime I see a movie with babies. I watched "Waitress" the other night and sobbed the whole freakin' movie. I dont think I'm like, outwardly, walking around "poor me" depressed. It feels more like a deep melancholia that I can't shake off. I really dont even know what to do about it. I thought maybe just writing it down here would help, but I dont think it did. Hhhmm...

I dreamt last night that I was walking home from a party or something late at night in BG. I was in a dark alley and there was a group of guys coming towards me. One of them came at me and I started running away, dialing 911 on my cell phone. He caught me and was trying to rip my clothes off but I managed to get away. I got turned around in the back streets and was trying to get somewhere with people and light, cause I think he was still following me. I ran into the lobby of a building that I THINK was a dorm. There were people in the lobby area and they were so not helpful. I made a phone call and then Nat came into the lobby to pick me up. I ran over to her, threw my arms around her and started sobbing. Then I woke up.  What is with my crazy-ass dreams?

In all my Heron excitement, I totally forgot: Idina Menzel, my freakin' hero, the woman I would leave my husband for, is going to be playing a concert in Detroit.  Mighican.  As in, less than an hour from me. My stupid husband has put his foot down though, and said I absolutely cannot go alone since it's Detroit. I dont care, if I cant find someone to go with me, I'll go anyway. There'll probably be yelling. But it's IDINA MENZEL PEOPLE!!! Grrr.....

Oh my god, did I have a good weekend?? Yes I did!  :) The Great Blue Heron music festival in Sherman NY. I highly recommend to anyone who enjoys live music, great people, drinking, etc. It's like Woodstock only without the acid. :) There is constantly music everywhere. Main stage, dance tent, and people just jamming with each other.  It was the most fun I've had in quite awhile. :) I also got kinda drunk! That probably helped!! And no worries about my social anxiety, cause everyone at the Heron is a total cool hippie! People just chatted with you. It kicked ass. I miss it already!!! 364 more days til the next one!

Yeah, and The Town Pants rule. Check 'em out if you find 'em online.
Natalie put a bucket on her head!!!

Stevie was amazing last night. :) Well, the hour, hour and a half we saw of her anyway! The concert was supposed to start at 730. Around 710 or so, JUST as we were pulling into a parking space, the skies opened and it started stormin' like mad. So we rushed through the rain to the concert hall, which I might add is an OPEN hall as its an outside amphitheater. I'm not sure when they opened the doors, but I'm thinking it was maybe, 815? Since they had to wait til the lightening stopped. Then we had to wait for the downpour to stop, which it did, for about 20 minutes. In that 20 minutes, they cleaned the stage, set up the instruments, etc, etc. Then guess what happened? Yep, starting pouring again. So the concert did not start til almost 1000. I dont think we got a whole show either, since the amphitheater is required to shut down at 1100pm because of neighbors. I think they played til almost 1130 though. I have never been so wet in my life. It rained the whole darn night. But Stevie was worth it. :) People were leaving left and right. Corey's like, maybe we should give up and leave, I'll bet they'll cancel it. I told him I had been waiting to see Stevie for months and I was not going anywhere without seeing her or being told to leave. :) It was awesome. And wet. But awesome.

Saturday night, when we were out getting dinner at a chinese buffet place, we ran into one of my exes. The ex I was totally mad about and wasnt that great of a friend, as he kinda just dumped me and everyone else everytime his ex called. But still, I was crazy about him. It was so weird. So weird. Even weirder (and good) was that looking at him, it was like, what on earth was I so crazy about? It was nice. I only have a few exes that I never really got closure with so it's nice. I think I only have one left. LOL. Its like it all happened in another life though. I feel a shock whenever I see the scars on my wrists because it was a different person entirely and for the life of me I cannot remember that horrid feeling. I still get depressed and anxious, but nowhere near as bad. Probably because of Corey. :) Still. I sometimes wonder when I meet new people, if they notice the scars and what they must think of me. Like, I'm a leper or something. :) I need to find some of that....is it vitman A that is supposed to minimize scarring?

Why are all my dreams about being captured, or held hostage and rescued? I have these dreams all the time! And most of the time, they linger and they make me feel all good inside! How WEIRD is that?? I want to be held hostage? Or maybe I want to be rescued? Shikes. Someone explain that weird-ass dream to me. In some of the dreams I'm rescued and in some I'm not. I am so weird. Seriously. I think a link broke in my brain and made me different from other humans, like I'm an alien or something.

Ever wonder if the dreams you have are the real world and when we're awake THAT'S actually the dream? I wonder that a lot.

I really  hope that the last post was under a cut. I cant tell sometimes. I'd feel bad if I posted that whole huge long thing without a cut.

I feel sometimes like I'm watching myself on tv. I think I may be losing touch with reality.

They are wonderful. :) Especially my best friend who is always so positive. I really need that, too, because honestly, right now I feel like I must have done something to pi** God off in another life or something because nothing good ever happens to Corey and I. No matter how hard we try, life just keeps finding new ways to throw sh** in front of us. I try my hardest to stay positive and keep reminding myself that no matter what, I married the man of my dreams, but some days it's like, SIGH. Seriously. SIGH.

I miss my neice so much. I know I can go see her whenever I want, but its not the same. Sniff. And really, I cant hold her right now since we were stupid on Memorial Day and spent the day outside with no sunscreen. I am so burned right now. My shoulders, arms, neck, chest and weirdly, a big patch right above my left knee. It freaking hurts. Damn sun.

Oh. And our renters fell through for our Maumee house. We're back to square 1. Yey my life. What the heck did I do to karma? Seriously?

Mom says that Willow is so happy and peaceful in the mornings. Maybe with her. With me, its fussing and I have no idea what she wants. None. She doesnt want food, she's clean, she just got up (well, that was a while ago). She's sleeping now. Thank the lord. She was just tired! Already. She slept from 7 last nite til about 730 this morning. I am so freaking tired.

Why must all the radio stations constantly remind me of the Three Doors Down concert that I can't afford? It's as if they know that they're one of my favorite bands. Sniff. I kinda gave up the option to buy tickets when Corey let me buy good seats to Stevie.

Not trashy for a 15 year old to pose topless. Sure. I can see how one might think that would not be skanky. If one has the IQ of a peanut.

I had an awesome time on Friday night, even though I DID have to work at 10 on Saturday. But the clubs in BG are so much fun. :) I drank a lot, but I tried that Chaser stuff for hangovers and it actually works! I felt ok on Saturday! A little tired, but I did only get 6 hours or so of sleep and I'm used to way more. LOL. The bride to be had a great time too and my sister is so freaking funny when she's drunk. She was our official "Pecker Inspector" (she had a badge!) and she kept asking guys if she could inspect their, well, you know! Hee hee. 

We bought our plane tickets for Florida and I'm a bit freaked. I am so utterly terrified of flying. I'm waffling back and forth between a little excited and horridly scared.

Corey is not going with me to OCTA state competetion this year and it makes me sad. :( There's a dance and I will be on the sidelines, sighing. I'm going to have to find someone to attach myself to so I wont be a lone loser. :) At least it's in Columbus!! I know people there. :)

I'm pretty excited, since I feel so old, but I have to pull out my younger self for this since we'll definetely be drinking heavily and I have to work at 10 am tomorrow. I did it in my early 20's, I can do it again in my late 20's!

I am super excited. Corey got the week off work that he requested for August and we've officially booked our hotel rooms in Orlando! It's set now. :) :) All we have left to do is get tickets for attractions. That may take some research. We have to find some decent deals. Our only problem is that we want to go to Disney, Epcot, Universal and SeaWorld and I am not sure we can afford all 4 so we may have to choose a few. ANd I hate choosing between 4 places I am dying to go. So, cross your fingers!

That's all. Oh! My brother and Alie are going to England next month and Corey and I get Willow for 6 days!!! WooHoo!!!

I had something I was going to post, but now I've forgotten it in the panic of the moment. My renter for our Maumee house is leaving at the end of May. We have no one else lined up nor have we had ANY bites on selling it. I'm doing my absolute best to make my husband's life simpler, by not spending money, not complaining about what we dont have, giving stuff up for him, whatever, but there is one thing that I cannot and will not do. I will not move back to Maumee. I hated it there, and I love it in Perrysburg. I'd rather live in a smaller apartment than back in that house. I hate doing that to my hubby, but I just cant do it. I cant. So now....we're kinda at a loss...Hmmm...

Oh, and the IRS is taking almost a $1000 of our money all at once. Yep. We OWE this year. GOD I HATE THE GOVERNMENT! Why doesnt the IRS just go ahead and come to my house and rob me at gunpoint, cause that's exactly what they're doing. Yeah, I dont care who reads this, the government sucks.

Then I realized that 21 rows away from Stevie Nicks is Not Too Shabby. :) 

And that has been my morning.

I totally had this hot dream about Locke, a guy on "Lost". If you watch "Lost" you'd know him. He was always cute, but after my dream, he is now the hottest guy on the show and the fact that they didnt show him at all in the last episode totally annoyed me. :) 

My dream was that I'd been kidnapped, by like, 2-3 girls who were really dumb and for some reason I had access to a cell phone. So I called Locke and screamed at him "Help, I've been kidnapped" before they took the cell phone with me. And then, for some reason, I got ahold of the cell phone again and called him again to give him clues to where I was. Then the girls decided to kill me and a few other captives (because for some reason, there were other kidnappee's) and while I was on my knees, I saw Locke sneak into the room. He came up behind the girl who was about to kill me, and she was so dumb, she didnt hear or see him, so he stood behind her and crossed his arms, waiting for her to realize he was there. :) Then he saved me, and now he's freaking gorgeous to me. He was always hot. But now, wooooooo....:) 

Sigh. What a dream.

I feel like I've been severely depressed and suddenly I'm on Prozak! Its odd.

Only some people. Not all people. People who suck are people who run into other people. They suck. Some a**hole in an F150 ran into me at a light the other day. Best part? He didnt even get cited for it. He told the cops I ran a red light!!! I so did not. I was going through the intersection and it had turned yellow while I was going through it. It turned red about 3/4 of the way through and everyone in front of me was going super slowly cause of the roads (slippery). And so his light turned green and he was like, I'm going! And then slowly crept forward and hit me. Looked right at me and hit me. The cop was like "There were no witnesses and you both are saying you had the right of way so no one is getting cited". I was so furious. And now my perfect little Focus is crunchy in the front. :( Its not AWFUL. Its mostly cosmetic and my hood is about half-inch crunched up. My lights are a bit off line.
